docs.label: MCD charges ₹20 per hour for cars, up to ₹100 per 24 hours. Payment via QR code, UPI, or card through the MyParkings app is accepted.
MCD charges ₹10 per hour for two-wheelers, up to ₹50 per 24 hours. Payment via QR code, UPI, or card through the MyParkings app is accepted.
Use the Smart Parking app or website to view real-time availability as vehicles book or exit.
Open the Smart Parking app, select your location and slot, then confirm booking. Payment can be made via QR code, UPI, or card.
Check your registered email or phone number. If the issue persists, try resending via the Smart Parking app or contact support.
Yes, you can pay using QR code through the MyParkings app at all MCD parking lots.
Report overcharging to MCD via their helpline or the MyParkings app feedback. Contractors must follow official rates.
Yes, MCD reserves parking spots for disabled: 3% for disabled and 5% for women drivers.
Yes, MCD has multi-level and puzzle parking lots in areas such as Janakpuri to reduce congestion.
MCD allots parking lots through e-tenders and license fee auctions. Contractors manage lots digitally via the MyParkings app.
